President Muhammadu Buhari said about 50 million Nigerians will get their unique National Identification Numbers [NINs] before December ending. President Buhari disclosed this yesterday in Abuja during the opening ceremony of a 3-day ID4Africa forum being hosted by Nigeria. He said by 2019 over 70m Nigerians and legal residents would have been added to the identity database in custody of the National Identity Management Commission [NIMC]. The President who was represented by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation [SGF], Mr Boss Gida Mustapha said government has recognized the need to have a single national identity.